{"questionId": "ad300285-6ff9-46a9-97ab-7356c9cd2965_17", "correctAnswer": "9", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Set up the intercept", "content": "The $y$-intercept of $y=f(x)$ occurs where $x=0$, so evaluate $f(0)$."}, {"title": "Solve for the value", "content": "Substituting gives $$f(0)=-9(0)+9=9.$$ The answer is <strong>9</strong>.", "desmosExpressions": ["y = -9x + 9", "(0, 9)"]}]}